# Enhanced Mobile App Development Prompts

Here are the improved, production-ready prompts for systematic mobile app development:

---

## üöÄ PROMPT 1: Implementation Prompt

```
MOBILE APP DEVELOPMENT - SESSION IMPLEMENTATION

Session: M0.1 (or specify session number)

CONTEXT:
Review all mobile app documentation in the notes/ folder:
- MOBILE-PHASES-DETAILED.md (session requirements and deliverables)
- MOBILE-APP-MAIN.md (overall architecture and specifications)
- MOBILE-BRANDING-SUMMARY.md (Yellow Power International branding)
- MOBILE-WIREFRAMES.md (UI/UX design specifications)
- MOBILE-BUILD-DEPLOY.md (build and deployment procedures)
- MOBILE-EXPO-GO-TESTING.md (testing workflows)

OBJECTIVE:
Systematically implement Session M0.1 from MOBILE-PHASES-DETAILED.md to 100% completion with production-ready quality.

REQUIREMENTS:
1. Follow the exact session scope, deliverables, and Definition of Done from MOBILE-PHASES-DETAILED.md
2. Apply Yellow Power International branding consistently:
   - Primary: #FDB913 (Yellow Power Gold)
   - Secondary: #003366 (Navy Blue)
   - Typography: Inter font family
   - All component styles per MOBILE-WIREFRAMES.md
3. Implement all features as production-ready code (not prototypes or placeholders)
4. Include comprehensive error handling and edge cases
5. Add TypeScript types for all components and functions
6. Follow React Native and Expo best practices
7. Ensure offline-first capabilities where specified
8. Implement proper security measures (SecureStore for tokens, input validation)

FILE ORGANIZATION:
- Development code: dev/mobile/
- Production builds/scripts: prod-mobile/
- Documentation: notes/
- Configuration: dev/mobile/ (app.json, eas.json, theme.config.ts)

DELIVERABLES CHECKLIST:
‚ñ° All items from session "Deliverables" section completed
‚ñ° All Definition of Done criteria met
‚ñ° Code follows TypeScript strict mode
‚ñ° Components use Yellow Power branding
‚ñ° Error handling implemented
‚ñ° Loading states implemented
‚ñ° Offline handling (if applicable)
‚ñ° Comments added for complex logic
‚ñ° No console errors or warnings
‚ñ° Tested on Expo Go (iOS and Android)

TESTING REQUIREMENTS:
‚ñ° Test on physical device via Expo Go
‚ñ° Verify all user interactions work
‚ñ° Test error scenarios
‚ñ° Test offline mode (if applicable)
‚ñ° Verify branding colors are correct
‚ñ° Check typography renders properly
‚ñ° Test on both iOS and Android

OUTPUT:
1. Implement all session requirements
2. Create/update necessary files in dev/mobile/
3. Update session status in MOBILE-PHASES-DETAILED.md
4. Document any API requirements for backend team
5. Provide Expo Go QR code command for testing
6. List any dependencies or blockers

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
Session is considered 100% complete when:
‚úì All deliverables implemented and functional
‚úì All Definition of Done items checked off
‚úì Code is production-ready (no TODOs, no placeholders)
‚úì Tested successfully on both iOS and Android
‚úì Branding applied correctly throughout
‚úì No breaking bugs or critical issues
‚úì Documentation updated

Begin implementation now.
```

---

## üîç PROMPT 2: Verification Prompt

```
MOBILE APP DEVELOPMENT - SESSION VERIFICATION

Session: M0.1 (or specify session number)

CONTEXT:
Verify the completion status of Session M0.1 against all requirements.

REVIEW SOURCES:
1. MOBILE-PHASES-DETAILED.md - Session requirements and DoD
2. MOBILE-APP-MAIN.md - Architecture and specifications
3. MOBILE-BRANDING-SUMMARY.md - Branding compliance
4. MOBILE-WIREFRAMES.md - UI/UX specifications
5. dev/mobile/ - Implementation codebase
6. Expo Go testing results

VERIFICATION CHECKLIST:

A. DELIVERABLES VERIFICATION:
   ‚ñ° Review each deliverable from session specification
   ‚ñ° Confirm all files exist in correct locations
   ‚ñ° Verify code quality and completeness
   ‚ñ° Check for placeholder code or TODOs
   ‚ñ° Validate TypeScript types are complete

B. DEFINITION OF DONE VERIFICATION:
   ‚ñ° Go through each DoD item systematically
   ‚ñ° Test each criterion on physical device
   ‚ñ° Document pass/fail for each item
   ‚ñ° Identify any gaps or issues

C. BRANDING VERIFICATION:
   ‚ñ° Primary buttons use #FDB913 (Yellow Power Gold)
   ‚ñ° Secondary buttons use #003366 (Navy Blue)
   ‚ñ° Inter font family loaded and applied
   ‚ñ° Active states use correct colors
   ‚ñ° Status badges use semantic colors
   ‚ñ° Typography follows specifications
   ‚ñ° Spacing and layout match design system

D. FUNCTIONALITY VERIFICATION:
   ‚ñ° All features work as specified
   ‚ñ° Error handling covers edge cases
   ‚ñ° Loading states display correctly
   ‚ñ° Offline mode works (if applicable)
   ‚ñ° Navigation flows smoothly
   ‚ñ° Forms validate properly
   ‚ñ° API calls succeed/fail gracefully

E. TESTING VERIFICATION:
   ‚ñ° Tested on iOS device via Expo Go
   ‚ñ° Tested on Android device via Expo Go
   ‚ñ° No console errors or warnings
   ‚ñ° Performance is acceptable
   ‚ñ° No memory leaks or crashes

F. CODE QUALITY VERIFICATION:
   ‚ñ° TypeScript strict mode passes
   ‚ñ° ESLint shows no errors
   ‚ñ° Code follows React Native best practices
   ‚ñ° Components are reusable and maintainable
   ‚ñ° Proper separation of concerns
   ‚ñ° No hardcoded values (use theme/config)

OUTPUT REQUIRED:

1. COMPLETION STATUS:
   - Overall completion percentage (0-100%)
   - Status: Complete / Incomplete / Needs Revision

2. GAPS IDENTIFIED:
   List all missing items, incomplete features, or issues:
   - [ ] Gap 1: Description and location
   - [ ] Gap 2: Description and location
   - [ ] Gap 3: Description and location

3. ISSUES FOUND:
   - Critical: (blocks production deployment)
   - Major: (significant functionality issues)
   - Minor: (polish and improvements)

4. FIX-IT PROMPT:
   If session is not 100% complete, generate a detailed prompt:
   
   ```
   MOBILE APP DEVELOPMENT - FIX SESSION M0.1

   GAPS TO ADDRESS:
   1. [Specific gap with file location]
   2. [Specific gap with file location]
   
   ISSUES TO FIX:
   - Critical: [Issue description]
   - Major: [Issue description]
   - Minor: [Issue description]

   REQUIREMENTS:
   [Specific requirements to meet 100% completion]

   ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
   [Updated criteria based on gaps]

   Implement all fixes to bring Session M0.1 to 100% production-ready status.
   ```

5. RECOMMENDATIONS:
   - Suggestions for improvement
   - Best practices to apply
   - Optimization opportunities

Begin verification now and provide detailed results.
```

