## üì¶ PROMPT 3: Deployment Prompt

```
MOBILE APP DEVELOPMENT - DEPLOYMENT & COMMIT

Session: M0.1 (or specify session number)

CONTEXT:
Review completed Session M0.1 implementation and prepare for deployment.

PRE-DEPLOYMENT CHECKLIST:

A. CODE REVIEW:
   ‚ñ° All session deliverables completed
   ‚ñ° No TODOs or placeholder code
   ‚ñ° TypeScript compilation successful
   ‚ñ° No ESLint errors or warnings
   ‚ñ° Code follows project conventions

B. TESTING VERIFICATION:
   ‚ñ° Tested on iOS via Expo Go
   ‚ñ° Tested on Android via Expo Go
   ‚ñ° All features functional
   ‚ñ° No critical bugs
   ‚ñ° Performance acceptable

C. BRANDING VERIFICATION:
   ‚ñ° Yellow Power International colors applied
   ‚ñ° Inter font family working
   ‚ñ° UI matches design specifications

D. IMPACT ANALYSIS:
   Determine if changes affect:
   ‚ñ° Mobile app only (dev/mobile/)
   ‚ñ° Backend (dev/backend/) - API changes, new endpoints
   ‚ñ° Frontend (dev/frontend/) - shared components, types
   ‚ñ° Documentation (notes/)

DEPLOYMENT TASKS:

1. GIT OPERATIONS:
   
   A. Stage Mobile App Changes:
   ```bash
   cd C:\Users\Plange\Downloads\Projects\mining-erp
   
   # Stage mobile app files
   git add dev/mobile/
   git add notes/MOBILE-*.md
   git add prod-mobile/ (if exists)
   
   # Check what's staged
   git status
   ```

   B. Commit Mobile App Changes:
   ```bash
   git commit -m "Mobile App: Complete Session M0.1 - [Brief Description]

   Session M0.1 Deliverables:
   - [Deliverable 1]
   - [Deliverable 2]
   - [Deliverable 3]

   Changes:
   - [Specific change 1]
   - [Specific change 2]

   Testing:
   - Tested on iOS via Expo Go
   - Tested on Android via Expo Go
   - All DoD criteria met

   Branding: Yellow Power International (#FDB913, #003366, Inter font)
   Status: Production-ready"
   ```

   C. Push to GitHub:
   ```bash
   git push origin main
   ```

2. BACKEND/FRONTEND CHANGES (if applicable):
   
   IF Session M0.1 required backend API changes:
   ```bash
   # Stage backend changes separately
   git add dev/backend/src/
   
   git commit -m "Backend: API endpoints for Mobile Session M0.1

   New Endpoints:
   - [Endpoint 1]
   - [Endpoint 2]

   Changes:
   - [Change description]

   Related to: Mobile App Session M0.1"
   
   git push origin main
   ```

   IF Session M0.1 required frontend changes:
   ```bash
   # Stage frontend changes separately
   git add dev/frontend/
   
   git commit -m "Frontend: Updates for Mobile Session M0.1

   Changes:
   - [Change description]

   Related to: Mobile App Session M0.1"
   
   git push origin main
   ```

3. VPS DEPLOYMENT (if backend/frontend changed):
   
   Connect via PuTTY:
   - Host: 216.158.230.187
   - Port: 22
   - Username: root
   - Password: =2pcZVgDY8Ad5PRK6r

   Run deployment commands:
   ```bash
   # Navigate to project
   cd /var/www/mining-erp
   
   # Pull latest changes
   git pull origin main
   
   # Update Backend (if changed)
   cd dev/backend
   npm ci
   npm run build
   npx prisma generate
   pm2 restart erp-backend
   
   # Update Frontend (if changed)
   cd ../frontend
   npm ci
   npm run build
   pm2 restart erp-frontend
   
   # Verify
   pm2 status
   pm2 logs erp-backend --lines 20
   pm2 logs erp-frontend --lines 20
   ```

4. EXPO GO TESTING:
   
   Generate QR code for testing:
   ```bash
   cd C:\Users\Plange\Downloads\Projects\mining-erp\dev\mobile
   
   # Start development server
   npm start
   
   # Alternative: Use tunnel for different networks
   npm start -- --tunnel
   
   # Alternative: Clear cache if needed
   npm start -- --clear
   ```

   Testing Instructions:
   1. Open Expo Go app on your phone
   2. Scan the QR code displayed in terminal
   3. App will load with Session M0.1 changes
   4. Test all new features
   5. Verify branding is correct
   6. Check for any errors

OUTPUT REQUIRED:

1. CHANGE SUMMARY:
   - Mobile app changes: [List files changed]
   - Backend changes: [List if any, or "None"]
   - Frontend changes: [List if any, or "None"]

2. COMMIT DETAILS:
   - Commit hash: [After git commit]
   - Commit message: [Full message]
   - Files committed: [Count and list]

3. DEPLOYMENT STATUS:
   - GitHub push: Success/Failed
   - Backend deployment: Success/Failed/Not Applicable
   - Frontend deployment: Success/Failed/Not Applicable
   - Expo Go testing: QR code generated

4. VERIFICATION COMMANDS:
   Provide these commands for user to verify:
   ```bash
   # Check mobile app on Expo Go
   cd dev/mobile && npm start
   
   # Verify backend (if changed)
   curl https://erp.yellowpowerinternational.com/api/health
   
   # Verify frontend (if changed)
   # Visit: https://erp.yellowpowerinternational.com
   ```

5. POST-DEPLOYMENT CHECKLIST:
   ‚ñ° Mobile app loads on Expo Go
   ‚ñ° All Session M0.1 features working
   ‚ñ° Backend APIs responding (if changed)
   ‚ñ° Frontend pages loading (if changed)
   ‚ñ° No errors in logs
   ‚ñ° Branding correct

IMPORTANT NOTES:
- Only commit mobile app changes to GitHub
- Clearly separate mobile, backend, and frontend commits
- Test on Expo Go before marking as complete
- Document any breaking changes
- Update session status in MOBILE-PHASES-DETAILED.md

Begin deployment process now.
```

---

## üìù Usage Instructions

### For Each Session:

1. **Implementation Phase**: Use Prompt 1
   - Replace "M0.1" with current session (e.g., "M1.2", "M2.3")
   - Follow all requirements systematically
   - Ensure 100% completion before moving on

2. **Verification Phase**: Use Prompt 2
   - Verify against all documentation
   - Identify any gaps or issues
   - Generate fix-it prompt if needed

3. **Deployment Phase**: Use Prompt 3
   - Commit changes to GitHub
   - Deploy backend/frontend if affected
   - Test on Expo Go with QR code

### Session Progression:

```
M0.1 ‚Üí M0.2 ‚Üí M1.1 ‚Üí M1.2 ‚Üí M1.3 ‚Üí M1.4 ‚Üí M2.1 ‚Üí ... ‚Üí M7.3
```

Each session must be 100% complete before starting the next.

---

These enhanced prompts ensure systematic, production-ready development with proper verification and deployment procedures for the Mining ERP mobile app.